memberdef.name: INVALID_NUMERIC_LITERAL_SPECIFIED
memberdef.initializer: SyntaxError( \ "Given value ", std::quoted(VALUE), " is not an external representation of type ", \ demangle(typeid(*this)))

memberdef.name: UNSUPPORTED_ENUMERATION_VALUE_SPECIFIED
memberdef.initializer: SyntaxError( \ "Given value ", std::quoted(VALUE), \ " is valid OpenSCENARIO value of type " #TYPE ", but it is not supported yet")

memberdef.name: UNEXPECTED_ENUMERATION_VALUE_SPECIFIED
memberdef.initializer: SyntaxError("Unexpected value ", std::quoted(VALUE), " of type " #TYPE " was specified")

memberdef.name: UNEXPECTED_ENUMERATION_VALUE_ASSIGNED
memberdef.initializer: SyntaxError( \ "Unexpected value ", static_cast<TYPE::value_type>(VALUE), " was assigned to type " #TYPE)

memberdef.name: UNSUPPORTED_ELEMENT_SPECIFIED
memberdef.initializer: SyntaxError( \ "Given class ", ELEMENT, " is valid OpenSCENARIO element of class ", demangle(typeid(*this)), \ ", but is not supported yet")

memberdef.name: UNSUPPORTED_CONVERSION_DETECTED
memberdef.initializer: SyntaxError("Converting " #FROM " to " #TO \ ". This is valid in OpenSCENARIO standard, but is not yet supported")

memberdef.name: UNSUPPORTED_SETTING_DETECTED
memberdef.initializer: SyntaxError(#ACTION_OR_CONDITION " does not yet support ", ELEMENT)
